msgid "Images are born from pipelines"
msgstr "Las imágenes nacen de los pipelines"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/news/modules-groups-redesign/index.md:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "A pixel pipeline is a sequence of filters in which pixels are processed to end on a medium. Photoshop calls those filters [_layers_](https://helpx.adobe.com/photoshop/using/layer-basics.html), abiding by a methaphor inherited from paper and matte painting. Da Vinci Resolve, Blender, Natron, etc. calls them [_nodes_](https://filmmakingelements.com/everything-about-nodes-in-davinci-resolve/), abiding by a metaphor grounded in directed graphs and [flowcharts](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flowchart), best known to engineers. Both have a way of showing how those filters are organized, either with a layer stack or with the node graph (aka flowchart).\n"
msgstr "Un pipeline de píxeles es una secuencia de filtros en la que los píxeles se procesan para terminar en un medio. Photoshop llama a esos filtros [_capas_](https://helpx.adobe.com/photoshop/using/layer-basics.html), siguiendo una metáfora heredada del papel y la pintura opaca. Da Vinci Resolve, Blender, Natron, etc. los llaman [_nodos_](https://filmmakingelements.com/everything-about-nodes-in-davinci-resolve/), siguiendo una metáfora basada en grafos dirigidos y [diagramas de flujo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flowchart), bien conocidos por los ingenieros. Ambos tienen una manera de mostrar cómo se organizan esos filtros, ya sea con un apilamiento de capas o con el gráfico de nodos (también conocido como diagrama de flujo).\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/news/modules-groups-redesign/index.md:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "The important part is, __order matters__.\n"
msgstr "La parte importante es, __el orden importa__.\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/news/modules-groups-redesign/index.md:31
#, no-wrap
msgid "Darktable calls those filters modules. But \"modules\" refers to the [modular programming logic](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modular_programming) : each module is coded separately, using an uniform API, and doesn't know about the other modules. The pipeline itself doesn't know anything about the internals of modules, it only wires the inputs and the outputs. It's a clean way of developing, but it's completely irrelevant to the end-user.\n"
msgstr "Darktable llama a esos filtros módulos. Pero 'módulos' se refiere a la [lógica de programación modular](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modular_programming): cada módulo se codifica por separado, usando una API uniforme, y no conoce a los otros módulos. El pipeline en sí no sabe nada sobre los internals de los módulos, solo conecta las entradas y las salidas. Es una manera limpia de desarrollar, pero es totalmente irrelevante para el usuario final.\n"

